Scholz has been visiting China since Sunday, in his second visit since, at the end of 2021, he became Chancellor; before arriving in Beijing he was in Chongqing (southwest) and Shanghai economic capital. On the Ukrainian crisis, China calls for dialogue, opposes any use of nuclear weapons and urges respect for territorial integrity "of all countries" - which implies including Ukraine. But Beijing has never publicly condemned Moscow for the invasion of Ukraine and regularly invites to consider the security concerns of all parties, including Russia's security concerns against NATO. China and Russia have been approaching for more than a decade because of the common complaint of what they consider the "West Aegean" on the international scene. The two countries strengthened their economic, military and diplomatic cooperation after the invasion of Ukraine. Also last week Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov was in Beijing.
